   <text>
      <body>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40498304">
            <form>
               <orth>friasg</orth>
               <pron>[fðiɑsk]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[fðiɑsk] Note: bait thrown out when cuddy-fishing and working with a hand-net.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40502336">
            <form>
               <orth>tàbh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: hand-net.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40482968">
            <form>
               <orth>suaplais</orth>
               <pron>[su̜ɤpɫɑʃ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[su̜ɤpɫɑʃ] Note: an unappetizing mixture of food.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40480160">
            <form>
               <orth>ucsa</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: fully grown saithe.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40479296">
            <form>
               <orth>cudaig</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: cuddy.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40478720">
            <form>
               <orth>smallag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: next stage of the saithe after the cuddy (1 year old?).</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40476776">
            <form>
               <orth>soithean</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: bigger than the “smallag” [q.v.] (2-year old saithe?).</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40590824">
            <form>
               <orth>liugha</orth>
               <pron>[lʹu̜ə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[lʹu̜ə] Note: lythe.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40587584">
            <form>
               <orth>sgeit</orth>
               <pron>[sɡɛtʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[sɡɛtʹ] Note: skate.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40583264">
            <form>
               <orth>dallag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: a spotted dogfish.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40588232">
            <form>
               <orth>glupa</orth>
               <pron>[ɡɫu̜pə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɡɫu̜pə] Note: a pool left after the tide recedes.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40575128">
            <form>
               <orth>bànag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: sea-trout.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40547480">
            <form>
               <orth>mot</orth>
               <pron>[mɔ̃t]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[mɔ̃t] Note: canopy over the fire in a blackhouse.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40549208">
            <form>
               <orth>luidhear</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: hole in roof of blackhouse through which the smoke escaped.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40550936">
            <form>
               <orth>guitear</orth>
               <pron>[ɡu̜tʹɑð]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɡu̜tʹɑð] Note: a drain dug just inside the wall in a blackhouse, covered with flat stones, to collect any seepage through the wall.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40552448">
            <form>
               <orth>glut-lionadh</orth>
               <pron>[ɡɫu̜t̪lw̃ṉəɣ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɡɫu̜t̪lw̃ṉəɣ] Note: earth packing between double walls of blackhouse.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40555328">
            <form>
               <orth>ceangal</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “na ceangail”. Note: the couples in a roof.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40555544">
            <form>
               <orth>taobhan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “na taobhain”. Note: Pieces of timber laid across the couples in a blackhouse roof binding the couples together. Usually one near the ridge, one in the middle and one near the top of the wall.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40557128">
            <form>
               <orth>maide-feannaig</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: stick protruding from the thatch serving as a peg round which the “sioman” is put.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40559648">
            <form>
               <orth>ceairrle</orth>
               <pron>[cɑʴlʹə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[cɑʴlʹə] Quot.: ceairrle shiomain. Note: a round ball. [NOTES: the turned r used for the symbol which is unclear in the original.]</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40562600">
            <form>
               <orth>gath-drama</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: ridge-pole.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40564112">
            <form>
               <orth>spar-ghaoitheadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: stick put across the couples, under the ridge, to strengthen them.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40565696">
            <form>
               <orth>dragh</orth>
               <pron>[d̪ɾɤɣ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[d̪ɾɤɣ] Note: rope round the thatch about two feet above the top of the wall. The weights were hung on this rope and also the rope going over the top was looped round this anchor rope.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40567280">
            <form>
               <orth>gulman</orth>
               <pron>[ɡu̜ɫumɑṉ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɡu̜ɫumɑṉ] Note: cataract on the eye.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40568792">
            <form>
               <orth>sleamhnagan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: sty on the eye.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40570304">
            <form>
               <orth>smugrach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “smugrach uisge”. Note: drizzle.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40572032">
            <form>
               <orth>ciùchran</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: drizzle</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40572608">
            <form>
               <orth>fad</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “Fad bhìnn uaineach a’ latha” [fɑd̪vĩ:nʹũ̜ɑ̃nʹɑx]. Note: all day long.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40588088">
            <form>
               <orth>caisean-coimheach</orth>
               <pron>[kɑʃɑ̃ṉkɛ̃ɑx]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kɑʃɑ̃ṉkɛ̃ɑx] Note: a “rotach” – annual spell of very bad weather.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40583696">
            <form>
               <orth>flion</orth>
               <pron>[flw̃ṉ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[flw̃ṉ] Note: sleet.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40578512">
            <form>
               <orth>siolag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: sand-eel.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm40575416">
            <form>
               <orth>eun-ghuireag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: seems to be applied to the snipe on the wing from the description of the sound it makes at night.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37303144">
            <form>
               <orth>feannadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: a’ feannadh na mónach. Note: turfing.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37302784">
            <form>
               <orth>carcaire</orth>
               <pron>[kɑɾkəðə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kɑɾkəðə] Note: width of peat turfed for cutting.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37342816">
            <form>
               <orth>barr-fhad</orth>
               <pron>[bɑrɑd̪]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[bɑrɑd̪] Note: the top peat.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37320712">
            <form>
               <orth>corr-fhad</orth>
               <pron>[kɔrɑd̪]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kɔrɑd̪] Note: the second peat.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37317976">
            <form>
               <orth>caoran</orth>
               <pron>[kw:ɾɑṉ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kw:ɾɑṉ] Note: the third peat.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37323808">
            <form>
               <orth>iarunn-móineadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: peat-cutting iron.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37335400">
            <form>
               <orth>sgaoilteach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: area on higher level where peats are spread to dry.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37313224">
            <form>
               <orth>fàd-iomaill</orth>
               <pron>[fɑ:dĩmilʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[fɑ:dĩmilʹ] Quot.: a’ fàd-iomaill. Note: the outer peat.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37341592">
            <form>
               <orth>gàradh-gréineadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: peat wall on the edge of the bank (2nd peat).</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37347928">
            <form>
               <orth>coilleag</orth>
               <pron>[kɤlʹɑɡ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kɤlʹɑɡ] Note: when first lifted 4-5 peats are made into a “coilleag”.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37335688">
            <form>
               <orth>coilleagachadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: a’ coilleagachadh. Note: making “coilleagan” [q.v.] of peats when lifted.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37307176">
            <form>
               <orth>rùbhan</orth>
               <pron>[ru̜:ɑṉ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ru̜:ɑṉ] Note: several “coilleagan” [q.v.] of peats put together to form a “rùbhan”. [NOTES: corrected to ‘rùghan’ on the slip.]</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37323160">
            <form>
               <orth>iris</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: creel-band.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37321360">
            <form>
               <orth>breugan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: gap left in the weaving of the creel a few inches from the top. (Plural breugan.)</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37349872">
            <form>
               <orth>staing</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: main wand in a creel.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37327840">
            <form>
               <orth>gniomhadh</orth>
               <pron>[ɡðĩɤ̃vəɣ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[ɡðĩɤ̃vəɣ] Note: the outer shell of the peatstack, built to a brickwork pattern.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37303504">
            <form>
               <orth>sgàindeach</orth>
               <pron>[sɡɑ̃:nʹdʹɑx]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[sɡɑ̃:nʹdʹɑx] Note: uncut peat which is dry enough for burning. Also applied to a dried cow’s dropping used for fuel.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37343320">
            <form>
               <orth>ceum</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “an ceum”. Note: the “step” of the ‘cas-chrom’.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37305952">
            <form>
               <orth>raoin</orth>
               <pron>[rw̃:nʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[rw̃:nʹ] Note: a field.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37328272">
            <form>
               <orth>ceann-iomaire</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: end-rig, where horses turned when ploughing.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37313656">
            <form>
               <orth>sgrìllig</orth>
               <pron>[sɡɾı:lʹiɡʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[sɡɾı:lʹiɡʹ] Note: very small potato.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37308688">
            <form>
               <orth>sìlean</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: very small potato.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37322800">
            <form>
               <orth>cipean-tochail</orth>
               <pron>[cıpɑṉt̪ɔxəl]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[cıpɑṉt̪ɔxəl] Note: trial of strength similar to the ‘maide-leisg’.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37338280">
            <form>
               <orth>spungag</orth>
               <pron>[spũ̜ŋɡɑɡ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[spũ̜ŋɡɑɡ] Note: sling (for firing stones).</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37307824">
            <form>
               <orth>leum</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: “leum a’ bhradain”. Note: twisting oneself into the air from a position flat on one’s back on the ground or floor.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37328920">
            <form>
               <orth>leum-sùrdag</orth>
               <pron>[lemsu̜:ʴsd̪ɑɡ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[lemsu̜:ʴsd̪ɑɡ] Note: jumping with both feet together. [NOTES: the turned r used for the symbol which is unclear in the original.]</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37336984">
            <form>
               <orth>roid</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: sprint.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37324816">
            <form>
               <orth>leum-roid</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: a running jump.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37311280">
            <form>
               <orth>fàinne</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: a’ deanamh fàinne a’ cholair. Note: straw part collar made by winding “sioman” round a core of straw, [kɑ̃ũ̜ɫɑx]. When it was long enough, the two ends were brought together so that it formed the shape of the collar. It was judged to be of the right size if the arm fitted into it with fingers outstretched, the elbow resting inside the base and the tips of the fingers touching the top where the two ends met. Probably the core of the collar.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37335832">
            <form>
               <orth>muiseal</orth>
               <pron>[mũ̜ʃɑɫ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[mũ̜ʃɑɫ] Quot.: “muiseal a’ chruinn”. Note: the “muzzle” of the plough.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37317616">
            <form>
               <orth>plàta</orth>
               <pron>[pɫɑ:d̪ə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[pɫɑ:d̪ə] Note: blanket put under saddle.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37318048">
            <form>
               <orth>spòg</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: spògan a’ chruinn. Note: the arms of the plough.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm154564480">
            <form>
               <orth>gobhal</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot. “gobhal a’ chruinn”. Note: in between the two arms of the plough.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm154565416">
            <form>
               <orth>muing</orth>
               <pron>[mũ̜ɲɡʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[mũ̜ɲɡʹ] Note: horse’s mane.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm154560016">
            <form>
               <orth>sguab</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: sguab coirc, sguab eòrna.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm154564624">
            <form>
               <orth>beum</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: the amount one would cut with one stroke of the scythe.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37703968">
            <form>
               <orth>spagh</orth>
               <pron>[spɤɣ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[spɤɣ] Note: swathe.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idm37673728">
            <form>
               <orth>adag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: adag eòrna, adag coirc.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3355232">
            <form>
               <orth>toit</orth>
               <pron>[t̪ɔtʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[t̪ɔtʹ] Quot.: toit coirc, toit eòrna. Note: “hut”, containing aobut twenty stooks.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3357176">
            <form>
               <orth>tùisde</orth>
               <pron>[t̪u̟:ʃdʹə]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[t̪u̟:ʃdʹə] Note: flail.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3358904">
            <form>
               <orth>doid</orth>
               <pron>[d̪ɔdʹ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[d̪ɔdʹ] Note: a very small, low haycock. Might have 12 of these in a proper-sized haycock.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3360632">
            <form>
               <orth>coc</orth>
               <pron>[kɔxk]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[kɔxk] Quot.: coc fheòir. Note: haycock.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3362576">
            <form>
               <orth>dais</orth>
               <pron>[d̪ɑʃ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[d̪ɑʃ] Quot.: dais fheòir. Note: haystack (loaf-shaped).</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3365384">
            <form>
               <orth>bachallag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Note: potato shoot.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3366896">
            <form>
               <orth>dìthean</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: dìthean a’ bhuntàta. Note: the flower on the potato shaw.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AJSmith_ScaristaFMacKenziemisc-idp3368624">
            <form>
               <orth>sloc</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quot.: sloc bhuntàta. Note: potato pit.</def>
         </entry>
